</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2755797B758FFA3C589CDDE3D18FA62" box="[495,559,1484,1510]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
posses a shallow groove in the dorsoapical part of phallus (
<figureCitation id="13092A7BB758FFA3C091CDDE3E2FF98A" captionStart="FIGURES 1 ­ 10" captionStartId="4.[264,383,1831,1855]" captionTargetBox="[355,1246,605,1809]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[352,1252,603,1813]" captionText="FIGURES 1 ­ 10: Male genitalia. 1 ­ 2: Plateros kalamensis sp. n.; 3 ­ 4: P. m a m a s e n s i s sp. n.; 5 ­ 6: P. milenae sp. n.; 7 ­ 8: P. orobuensis sp. n.; 9 ­ 10: P. tanatorajensis sp. n. Scale 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/155511/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Figs 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13092A7BB758FFA3C541CDE63E71F98A" box="[295,326,1524,1550]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 ­ 27. 11 ­ 13" captionStartId="5.[264,383,1721,1745]" captionTargetBox="[348,1240,494,1701]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[343,1242,494,1704]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 11 ­ 27. 11 ­ 13: Male genitalia. 11: Plateros rubromamasensis sp. n.; 12 ­ 13: P. lalui sp. n.; 14 ­ 19: Male pronota. 14: P. kalamensis sp. n.; 15: P. mamasensis sp. n.; 16: P. milenae sp. n.; 17: P. orobuensis sp. n.; 18: P. rubromamasensis sp. n.; 19: P. tanatorajensis sp. n.; 20: Female antenna. 20: P. flavidus Kleine, 1933; 21 ­ 27: Male antennae. 21: P. kalamensis sp. n.; 22: P. lalui sp. n.; 23: P. mamasensis sp. n.; 24: P. milenae sp. n.; 25: P. orobuensis sp. n.; 26: P. rubromamasensis sp. n.; 27: P. tanatorajensis sp. n. Scale 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/155512/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">11</figureCitation>
