<taxonomicName id="4C324D7DB758FFA3C758CDE63C8EF989" authority="Tvardik &amp; Bocak, 2001" authorityName="Tvardik &amp; Bocak" authorityYear="2001" box="[830,953,1524,1549]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Plateros" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milenae" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B946EAECB758FFA3C758CDE63C8EF989" box="[830,953,1524,1549]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">P. milenae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2755797B758FFA3C7A4CDE63B35F98A" box="[962,1026,1524,1550]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D7DB758FFA3C05BCDE63A1DF989" authority="Tvardik &amp; Bocak, 2001" authorityName="Tvardik &amp; Bocak" authorityYear="2001" box="[1085,1322,1524,1549]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Plateros" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubromamasensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B946EAECB758FFA3C05BCDE63A1DF989" box="[1085,1322,1524,1549]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">P. rubromamasensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2755797B758FFA3C56ECE0E3E71F9B2" box="[264,326,1564,1590]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is very similar in shape (
<figureCitation id="13092A7BB758FFA3C60DCE0E3DC6F9B2" box="[619,753,1564,1590]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 ­ 27. 11 ­ 13" captionStartId="5.[264,383,1721,1745]" captionTargetBox="[348,1240,494,1701]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[343,1242,494,1704]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 11 ­ 27. 11 ­ 13: Male genitalia. 11: Plateros rubromamasensis sp. n.; 12 ­ 13: P. lalui sp. n.; 14 ­ 19: Male pronota. 14: P. kalamensis sp. n.; 15: P. mamasensis sp. n.; 16: P. milenae sp. n.; 17: P. orobuensis sp. n.; 18: P. rubromamasensis sp. n.; 19: P. tanatorajensis sp. n.; 20: Female antenna. 20: P. flavidus Kleine, 1933; 21 ­ 27: Male antennae. 21: P. kalamensis sp. n.; 22: P. lalui sp. n.; 23: P. mamasensis sp. n.; 24: P. milenae sp. n.; 25: P. orobuensis sp. n.; 26: P. rubromamasensis sp. n.; 27: P. tanatorajensis sp. n. Scale 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/155512/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Figs 24, 26</figureCitation>
) and differs from the serrate antennomere 
<quantity id="4CCA9B1BB758FFA3C084CE0E3A38F9B2" box="[1250,1295,1564,1590]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" unit="in" value="3.0">3 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C324D7DB758FFA3C173CE0E3EA2F9D9" authority="Tvardik &amp; Bocak, 2001" authorityName="Tvardik &amp; Bocak" authorityYear="2001" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Plateros" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mamasensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B946EAECB758FFA3C173CE0E3EA2F9D9" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">P. mamasensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2755797B758FFA3C5F9CE563ED7F9DA" box="[415,480,1604,1630]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Both small and large eyes were found in this group. Already previous studies (e. g. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA34B0FB758FFA3C5CCCE7E3D44F902" author="Bocakova, M." box="[426,627,1644,1670]" firstAuthor="Bocakova" journalOrPublisher="Entomologica Basilensia" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" pagination="165 - 200" part="20" refId="ref6252" refString="Bocakova, M. (1997 a) Revision and phylogenetic analysis of the genus Melaneros Fairmaire, 1877 (Coleoptera, Lycidae) from New Guinea. Entomologica Basilensia, 20, 165 - 200." title="Revision and phylogenetic analysis of the genus Melaneros Fairmaire, 1877 (Coleoptera, Lycidae) from New Guinea" type="journal article" year="1997" yearSuffix="a">
Bocakova 
<number id="3DFA24D9B758FFA3C64ECE7E3D52F902" box="[552,613,1644,1670]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1997.0">1997</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA34B0FB758FFA3C6E7CE7E3DA6F902" author="Bocakova, M." box="[641,657,1644,1670]" journalOrPublisher="Acta Societatis Zoologicae Bohemiae" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" pagination="175 - 190" part="61" refId="ref6289" refString="Bocakova, M. (1997 b) Revision of the genus Melaneros from China with a note on Ditoneces (Coleoptera: Lycidae). Acta Societatis Zoologicae Bohemiae, 61, 175 - 190." title="Revision of the genus Melaneros from China with a note on Ditoneces (Coleoptera: Lycidae)" type="journal article" year="1997" yearSuffix="b">b</bibRefCitation>
) showed that eye size is variable within species groups and we expect that the eyes size is correlated with night flight activity.
</paragraph>
